verses.text: Now it came to pass, when the wall was built , and I had set up the doors , and the porters and the singers and the Levites were appointed ,
That I gave my brother Hanani , and Hananiah the ruler of the palace , charge over Jerusalem : for he \add was\add* a faithful man , and feared God above many.

And I said unto them, Let not the gates of Jerusalem be opened until the sun be hot ; and while they stand by , let them shut the doors , and bar \add them:\add* and appoint watches of the inhabitants of Jerusalem , every one in his watch , and every one \add to be\add* over against his house.
Now the city \add was\add* large and great : but the people \add were\add* few therein , and the houses \add were\add* not builded.\f + \fr 7.4 \ft large: Heb. broad in spaces\f* \p

¶ And my God put into mine heart to gather together the nobles , and the rulers , and the people , that they might be reckoned by genealogy. And I found a register of the genealogy of them which came up at the first , and found written therein,

These \add are\add* the children of the province , that went up out of the captivity , of those that had been carried away , whom Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon had carried away , and came again to Jerusalem and to Judah , every one unto his city ;

Who came with Zerubbabel , Jeshua , Nehemiah , Azariah , Raamiah , Nahamani , Mordecai , Bilshan , Mispereth , Bigvai , Nehum , Baanah. The number , \add I say\add*, of the men of the people of Israel \add was this;\add*\f + \fr 7.7 \ft Azariah: also called, Seraiah\f*
The children of Parosh , two thousand an hundred seventy and two.
The children of Shephatiah , three hundred seventy and two.
The children of Arah , six hundred fifty and two.
The children of Pahath-moab , of the children of Jeshua and Joab , two thousand and eight hundred \add and\add* eighteen.
The children of Elam , a thousand two hundred fifty and four.
The children of Zattu , eight hundred forty and five.
The children of Zaccai , seven hundred and threescore.
The children of Binnui , six hundred forty and eight.\f + \fr 7.15 \ft Binnui: also called, Bani\f*
The children of Bebai , six hundred twenty and eight.
The children of Azgad , two thousand three hundred twenty and two.
The children of Adonikam , six hundred threescore and seven.
The children of Bigvai , two thousand threescore and seven.
The children of Adin , six hundred fifty and five.
The children of Ater of Hezekiah , ninety and eight.
The children of Hashum , three hundred twenty and eight.
The children of Bezai , three hundred twenty and four.
The children of Hariph , an hundred and twelve.\f + \fr 7.24 \ft Hariph: also called, Jora\f*
The children of Gibeon , ninety and five.\f + \fr 7.25 \ft Gibeon: also called, Gibbar\f*
The men of Beth-lehem and Netophah , an hundred fourscore and eight.
The men of Anathoth , an hundred twenty and eight.
The men of Beth-azmaveth , forty and two.\f + \fr 7.28 \ft Beth-azmaveth: also called, Azmaveth\f*
The men of Kirjath-jearim , Chephirah , and Beeroth , seven hundred forty and three.\f + \fr 7.29 \ft Kirjath-jearim: also called, Kirjath-arim\f*
The men of Ramah and Geba , six hundred twenty and one.
The men of Michmas , an hundred and twenty and two.
The men of Beth-el and Ai , an hundred twenty and three.
The men of the other Nebo , fifty and two.
The children of the other Elam , a thousand two hundred fifty and four.
The children of Harim , three hundred and twenty.
The children of Jericho , three hundred forty and five.
The children of Lod , Hadid , and Ono , seven hundred twenty and one.
The children of Senaah , three thousand nine hundred and thirty. \p
¶ The priests : the children of Jedaiah , of the house of Jeshua , nine hundred seventy and three.
The children of Immer , a thousand fifty and two.
The children of Pashur , a thousand two hundred forty and seven.
The children of Harim , a thousand and seventeen. \p
¶ The Levites : the children of Jeshua , of Kadmiel , \add and\add* of the children of Hodevah , seventy and four.\f + \fr 7.43 \ft Hodevah: also called, Hodaviah or Judah\f* \p
¶ The singers : the children of Asaph , an hundred forty and eight. \p
¶ The porters : the children of Shallum , the children of Ater , the children of Talmon , the children of Akkub , the children of Hatita , the children of Shobai , an hundred thirty and eight. \p
¶ The Nethinims : the children of Ziha , the children of Hashupha , the children of Tabbaoth ,
The children of Keros , the children of Sia , the children of Padon ,
The children of Lebana , the children of Hagaba , the children of Shalmai ,
The children of Hanan , the children of Giddel , the children of Gahar ,
The children of Reaiah , the children of Rezin , the children of Nekoda ,
The children of Gazzam , the children of Uzza , the children of Phaseah ,
The children of Besai , the children of Meunim , the children of Nephishesim ,
The children of Bakbuk , the children of Hakupha , the children of Harhur ,
The children of Bazlith , the children of Mehida , the children of Harsha ,
The children of Barkos , the children of Sisera , the children of Tamah ,
The children of Neziah , the children of Hatipha. \p
¶ The children of Solomon’s servants : the children of Sotai , the children of Sophereth , the children of Perida ,
The children of Jaala , the children of Darkon , the children of Giddel ,
The children of Shephatiah , the children of Hattil , the children of Pochereth of Zebaim , the children of Amon.\f + \fr 7.59 \ft Amon: also called, Ami\f*
All the Nethinims , and the children of Solomon’s servants , \add were\add* three hundred ninety and two.

And these \add were\add* they which went up \add also\add* from Tel-melah , Tel-haresha , Cherub , Addon , and Immer : but they could not shew their father’s house , nor their seed , whether they \add were\add* of Israel.\f + \fr 7.61 \ft seed: or, pedigree\f*
The children of Delaiah , the children of Tobiah , the children of Nekoda , six hundred forty and two. \p

¶ And of the priests : the children of Habaiah , the children of Koz , the children of Barzillai , which took \add one\add* of the daughters of Barzillai the Gileadite to wife , and was called after their name.
These sought their register \add among\add* those that were reckoned by genealogy , but it was not found : therefore were they, as polluted , put from the priesthood.

And the Tirshatha said unto them, that they should not eat of the most holy things , till there stood \add up\add* a priest with Urim and Thummim.\f + \fr 7.65 \ft the Tirshatha: or, the governor\f* \p
¶ The whole congregation together \add was\add* forty and two thousand three hundred and threescore ,
Beside their manservants and their maidservants , of whom \add there were\add* seven thousand three hundred thirty and seven : and they had two hundred forty and five singing men and singing women.
Their horses , seven hundred thirty and six : their mules , two hundred forty and five :
\add Their\add* camels , four hundred thirty and five : six thousand seven hundred and twenty asses. \p

¶ And some of the chief of the fathers gave unto the work. The Tirshatha gave to the treasure a thousand drams of gold , fifty basons , five hundred and thirty priests’ garments.\f + \fr 7.70 \ft some: Heb. part.\f*\f + \fr 7.70 \ft The Tirshatha: or, the governor\f*
And \add some\add* of the chief of the fathers gave to the treasure of the work twenty thousand drams of gold , and two thousand and two hundred pound of silver.
And \add that\add* which the rest of the people gave \add was\add* twenty thousand drams of gold , and two thousand pound of silver , and threescore and seven priests’ garments.

So the priests , and the Levites , and the porters , and the singers , and \add some\add* of the people , and the Nethinims , and all Israel , dwelt in their cities ; and when the seventh month came , the children of Israel \add were\add* in their cities.
